-- 
Hungary Labor Unions, Civic Groups Pledge Strikes, MTI Reports

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-09-08T14:19:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/hungary-labor-unions-civic-groups-pledge-strikes-mti-reports.html
About 70 labor unions, civic and
social groups will begin strikes and protests on Sept. 29
against Prime Minister  Viktor Orban ’s plans to overhaul the
economy,  MTI  reported.  The groups are demanding a fairer distribution of the tax
burden, an end to retroactive laws, consultations on legislation
including a new labor law and the protection of the right to
strike and other union rights, the state news service said,
citing Peter Konya, head of the Law Enforcement Employees’
Interest Association.  To contact the reporters responsible for this story:
Zoltan Simon at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  